# Security

- Crypto / secret / auth / payment / data-access work: run Bugbot (`/review`) on the diff before presenting.
- Never log PII, tokens, passwords, or full payment data.
- Hardcoded secret found: stop, flag, redact as `<redacted>`, recommend rotation + git-history removal. Never propagate the value into any tool (memory, context7, web, external service).
- Secret-bearing files - `.env*`, `*.pem`, `*.pfx`, `*.p12`, `*.key`, and whatever config files the stack keeps secrets in - are sensitive: never read or echo their value by any route.
